# Implementation Plan: Advanced Resume Design & Accessibility Customization Tools

This document provides a complete technical blueprint and implementation checklist for another developer/agent to introduce granular layout, typography, color, spacing, and accessibility controls to **Seve**. 

It details how to allow users to customize almost all visual properties of their CV, map these settings to CSS Custom Properties, serialize them to the database, and support key accessibility overrides.

---

## 1. Architecture Overview & Customization Flow

The customization flow follows a clean "Data $\rightarrow$ State $\rightarrow$ CSS variables $\rightarrow$ DOM paint" pipeline:

```mermaid
graph TD
  A[User interacts with Left Panel Settings] --> B[React State Updates via ResumeContext]
  B --> C[Styles Sync to Supabase Database resume_data]
  B --> D[ResumePreview binds state to CSS Custom Variables style attribute]
  D --> E[TemplateRenderer / Sections read variables for layout rendering]
```

