## 2. Technical Specification

### A. Style Schema & Data Structures
We need to expand the styling fields of the active resume profile. Add these keys to the styling properties interface inside `src/types/resume.ts`:

```typescript
export interface ResumeStylePreferences {
  // Typography
  headingFont: string;       // 'Garamond', 'Outfit', 'Inter', 'Playfair Display', 'Fira Code'
  bodyFont: string;          // 'Inter', 'Lora', 'Roboto', 'OpenDyslexic'
  lineHeight: number;        // e.g. 1.15, 1.25, 1.4 (multipliers)
  letterSpacing: string;     // 'normal', 'wide', 'tight'
  headingCase: 'uppercase' | 'capitalize' | 'normal';

  // Spacing (Sliders)
  pagePadding: number;       // custom page margins (in mm: 10 to 24)
  sectionSpacing: number;    // margin-bottom between major sections (in px: 8 to 24)
  itemSpacing: number;       // spacing between job/education items (in px: 4 to 16)
  bulletIndent: number;      // bullet point left indent offset (in px: 12 to 24)

  // Colors & Borders
  bodyTextColor: string;     // Hex body color
  headingColor: string;      // Hex heading color
  dividerStyle: 'none' | 'solid' | 'dashed' | 'dotted';
  dividerWidth: number;      // border width (in px: 1 to 4)

  // Accessibility & Printing
  highContrastPrint: boolean;// force pure black/white text contrast for printers
  atsOptimizedFont: boolean; // override styling to standard Arial/Times fonts for ATS scanners
}
```

### B. Map to CSS Custom Variables
Inside `src/components/ResumePreview.tsx`, bind the new settings dynamically to the print wrapper container's style attribute:

```typescript
const computedStyles = {
  '--template-font-size': `${templateFontSize}px`,
  '--template-font-weight': templateFontWeight,
  '--template-heading-font': stylePrefs.headingFont,
  '--template-body-font': stylePrefs.bodyFont,
  '--template-line-height': stylePrefs.lineHeight,
  '--template-letter-spacing': stylePrefs.letterSpacing === 'wide' ? '0.05em' : stylePrefs.letterSpacing === 'tight' ? '-0.02em' : 'normal',
  '--template-heading-case': stylePrefs.headingCase,
  '--template-page-padding': `${stylePrefs.pagePadding}mm`,
  '--template-section-spacing': `${stylePrefs.sectionSpacing}px`,
  '--template-item-spacing': `${stylePrefs.itemSpacing}px`,
  '--template-bullet-indent': `${stylePrefs.bulletIndent}px`,
  '--template-body-color': stylePrefs.bodyTextColor,
  '--template-heading-color': stylePrefs.headingColor,
  '--template-divider-style': stylePrefs.dividerStyle,
  '--template-divider-width': `${stylePrefs.dividerWidth}px`,
  '--template-theme-color': themeColor,
} as React.CSSProperties;
```

