## 4. Implementation Step-by-Step Checklist

Another developer or agent should execute the implementation in this sequence:

### Phase 1: Database & Typings Schema
- [ ] **Database Migration**:
  - Run SQL script in Supabase to update the table schema. Ensure styling properties are included in the default JSON payload structure of `resume_data`.
- [ ] **Typings Update**:
  - Modify `src/types/resume.ts` to add the new style properties to the active profile interface type definitions.

### Phase 2: State Context Binding
- [ ] **Context Updates**:
  - Update `src/context/ResumeContext.tsx` to handle initial default values for these style keys when creating a blank resume template.
  - Update `src/layouts/EditorLayout.tsx` context states to bind all setter functions (e.g. `setHeadingFont`, `setPagePadding`) to update the active resume profile.
- [ ] **Mobile & Desk Sync**:
  - Ensure all layout preferences bind correctly to context props so changes are reflected in both desktop and mobile views.

### Phase 3: CSS Override Rules
- [ ] **CSS Updates**:
  - Modify `src/index.css` to define the base styles inside the print container reading from the new custom variables:
    ```css
    .resume-page {
      padding: var(--template-page-padding, 16mm) !important;
      font-family: var(--template-body-font, 'Inter'), sans-serif !important;
      line-height: var(--template-line-height, 1.2) !important;
      letter-spacing: var(--template-letter-spacing, normal) !important;
      color: var(--template-body-color, #334155) !important;
    }
    .resume-section {
      margin-bottom: var(--template-section-spacing, 12px) !important;
    }
    .resume-section-heading {
      font-family: var(--template-heading-font, 'Outfit'), serif !important;
      text-transform: var(--template-heading-case, uppercase) !important;
      color: var(--template-heading-color, var(--template-theme-color)) !important;
    }
    .resume-item {
      margin-bottom: var(--template-item-spacing, 8px) !important;
    }
    .resume-bullet-container {
      padding-left: var(--template-bullet-indent, 16px) !important;
    }
    .resume-divider {
      border-bottom-style: var(--template-divider-style, solid) !important;
      border-bottom-width: var(--template-divider-width, 1px) !important;
    }
    ```
- [ ] **Template Refactoring**:
  - Refactor all template rendering components in `src/components/ui/resume/` to ensure they use classes mapped to these variables (`resume-page`, `resume-section`, `resume-item`, etc.) rather than hardcoded Tailwind properties.

### Phase 4: UI Control Accordion Panel
- [ ] **Sidebar Forms inside `src/pages/EditorPage.tsx`**:
  - Refactored `renderDesignControls()` to build out themed accordion widgets using `framer-motion` for smooth height expansion.
  - Implement ranges and steps for inputs:
    - Margins: Range `10` to `24`, Step `1` (mm).
    - Section Gap: Range `6` to `28`, Step `2` (px).
    - Item Gap: Range `2` to `16`, Step `1` (px).
    - Line Height: Range `1.0` to `1.6`, Step `0.05` (multiplier).
    - Divider Size: Range `0.5` to `4.0`, Step `0.5` (px).
  - Implement font selections:
    - Headings: `Outfit` (Sans), `EB Garamond` (Classic Serif), `Playfair Display` (Elegant Serif), `JetBrains Mono` (Technical).
    - Body: `Inter` (Standard), `Roboto` (Clean Sans), `Lora` (Book Serif), `OpenDyslexic` (Dyslexia-friendly sans).

### Phase 5: PDF Capture Clone Updates
- [ ] **Off-screen capture cloning inside `src/utils/pdfExport.ts`**:
  - Ensure the offscreen cloning logic clones style variables. Check that inline style custom variables are copied to the printed node clone so the PDF downloads look identical to the customized on-screen canvas preview.

